Commentary: good length, and outside off. Cut off the back foot by Fakhar, but only to point
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full just outside off, the batsman lunges forward and defends. Played towards the off side
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: tossed up wide outside off, and Fakhar goes chasing after it. Manages to slice an expansive drive over point and the ball lands just inside the boundary. Could've easily gone for six too
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length, but wide outside off. Rocks back onto the back foot, and caresses the cut shot. Placed between point and the square-umpire with perfection
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: third four in a row! Good length on leg stump, but going down leg. Fakhar does well to swivel and flick this fine past short third man. Badree's line has been awry
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, punched off the back foot to mid on. They walk across for the run
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, angling into Fakhar. Defended off the front foot to mid on
Commentary_short: Paul to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: short outside off, but coming into Fakhar. Pokes his bat out and places this fine behind square. It's walloped past third man
Commentary_short: Paul to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on off stump and defended off the back foot. But that's a huge front-foot no ball! Free hit
Commentary_short: Paul to Fakhar Zaman, 1 no ball

Commentary: low full toss on middle stump, big wind up from Fakhar, but he mistimes it. Smacked back to the bowler. The leg-side slog does not come off
Commentary_short: Paul to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off. Angling into Fakhar again, and punched to cover
Commentary_short: Paul to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: good length on middle, and coming into his pads. Tries to flick it towards square leg, but misses. Hits his front leg, and trickles away to the off side
Commentary_short: Paul to Fakhar Zaman, 1 leg bye

Commentary: full just outside off, driven early, but falls short of cover. Good recovery from Keemo
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, tapped off the back foot to point
Commentary_short: Emrit to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: back of a length on middle, clipped off his pads to deep midwicket. Chase for the infielder, allowing Fakhar to come back for the second
Commentary_short: Emrit to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs

Commentary: good length on off stump, but Fakhar smacks this through the off-side field! Managed to carve it into the gap between point and cover point. Shifted his weight by walking down the wicket before playing that shot
Commentary_short: Emrit to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off, punched to mid on for a walking single. Misfield by the fielder, but the batsmen aren't interested to take another run
Commentary_short: Emrit to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, and pulled along the ground. Straight to deep midwicket. First runs
Commentary_short: Emrit to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, carves it past cover and chase for the infielder. Manages to retrieve it from inside the ropes
Commentary_short: Emrit to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs

Commentary: full outside off, driven away from his body, but mistimed. Only to cover
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length on middle, and turned off his hips to midwicket. Misfield by the infielder, that allows Babar two free runs. Went through Samuels' hands there
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: short and wide! Gets on top of this delivery, and cuts past backward point! No stopping that
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle, and going down leg. Babar shuffles across to the off side and drags this behind square on the leg side. Easily turned off his pads past deep backward square
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on off and angling right in. Punched off the back foot to mid on
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length on middle, turned off his pads to deep backward square. Man there
Commentary_short: Paul to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length, but slower. Tapped to the off side with soft hands, and Babar calls for the quick single
Commentary_short: Emrit to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, muscled down the ground to long on. They walk across for a run
Commentary_short: Emrit to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, but coming into Babar. Tries to cut it square but too close to his body. Past his outside edge
Commentary_short: Emrit to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length on off, stands tall and smacks this past midwicket! Muscled, and sent to the deep mid-wicket boundary
Commentary_short: Emrit to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length just outside off, punched off the back foot to cover
Commentary_short: Emrit to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: appeal for lbw, and given! The umpire took his time, but finally raised his finger. It was a yorker on leg stump, and Babar missed the leg-side flick. It hit his boot, and the only doubt was whether it was going down the leg side. Babar's not reviewing.
Commentary_short: Emrit to Babar Azam, OUT
Dismissal_text: Babar Azam lbw b Emrit 17 (13b 3x4 0x6) SR: 130.76

Commentary: full outside off, and driven to cover. The length was there for an expansive slog, but Fakhar couldn't get under it
Commentary_short: Williams to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off and that's too easy for the tall man. Cuts it past point, a very fluent shot
Commentary_short: Williams to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length just outside off, opens his bat's face and glances it to point. Calls for the single early
Commentary_short: Williams to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off. Talat lets his first ball go through to the keeper. Shoulders his arms this time
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: good length on off, stays slightly low but Talat manages to get his bat in front of his pads. Defended, but takes the bat's outside edge. Goes past short third man!
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, Talat nudges it to square leg with the ball angling past him. He'll keep strike
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: tossed up outside off. It's eventually a low full toss. Driven back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: drifty ball, and lands full on off stump. Tapped with soft hands towards the off side and they scamper across for the run
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: tossed up on middle, but Fakhar's happy to not fall for the trap. Driven down the ground to wide long off
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle, smacked past Badree's left to long on
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: first six! Muscled over long on. Full on off, and Fakhar takes a big stride forward to lean into that shot. Gives it a big swipe, and the ball lands in the stands
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, SIX runs

Commentary: full on off and spins away from Fakhar. Tries to prod at it, but the ball goes past his outside edge. Good recovery from Badree
Commentary_short: Badree to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: mix up! And Fakhar's stranded. Good length on off, and defended towards point. Talat's ball-watching and doesn't notice Fakhar halfway down the wicket. He tries to turn, and race back, but to no avail. The throw's at the top of the stumps, and easy work for the bowler backing up
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, OUT

Commentary: full on off stump, turned off his pads to fine leg. Gets the captain on strike
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, full and wide outside off. Gets his bat out, and taps it down to Badree at third man
Commentary_short: Williams to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: short on off, tries to defend off the back foot, but the ball takes the bottom edge. Almost played on!
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, but another slower ball. Defended with soft hands to the off side
Commentary_short: Williams to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: delicate! Back of a length outside off, and Sarfraz opens the bat's face this time. Runs it down fine, and the bowler's pace does the rest. Badree's effort at third man not good enough
Commentary_short: Williams to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: short ball, on off stump. Spinning away from Talat but he manages to drag this to the leg side. Played past midwicket
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: flat on middle stump, it's the one that goes straight through. Tries to flick towards square leg, but can't connect. Hits his pad as the ball goes to the leg side. Badree's interested for the review and he's convinced his captain. They're reviewing. Pitched on middle, but clipping the outside of leg stump. West Indies keep their review because that's umpire's call
Commentary_short: Badree to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 leg bye

Commentary: flighted full outside off, and that's been driven over the infield. Well hit, but there was protection at deep extra cover
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: short on middle. Sarfraz rocks back and tries to pull along the ground. Mistimed to midwicket
Commentary_short: Badree to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, he walks across to the off side and cuts it past point. Misfield from the man there means Talat wants the second. Could be a dangerous run, but he manages to scamper through eventually
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: full just outside off. Tries to open the bat's face and run it down to short third man. Misfield once again, but this time they're with just the single
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: starts his career with a wide. Good length, but way too much width
Commentary_short: Permaul to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: good length just outside off, cut to point on this occasion
Commentary_short: Permaul to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: good length, but awry. Wide outside off, and the keeper does well to get behind it
Commentary_short: Permaul to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: full just outside off, Talat shuffles across to the off side and cramps himself. Tapped back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Permaul to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: smacked past the bowler! Looks like Permaul has twisted his left ankle while trying to deliver. It was tossed up on middle, and Talat bunted this down the ground to the long-on boundary. Physio time
Commentary_short: Permaul to Hussain Talat, FOUR runs

Commentary: quick and short on middle. Tries to swivel and pull, but can't connect. Hits his thigh pad and goes down to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Samuels to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: over long on! A gentle length ball on middle, but Talat came down the ground to meet it on the full. Smacked safely into the long-on boundary
Commentary_short: Samuels to Hussain Talat, SIX runs

Commentary: good length just outside off. Tapped with soft hands to cover. Played in the gap, and Talat takes off for the single
Commentary_short: Samuels to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Quicker ball that Talat can't cut away. Through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: good length outside off again. Manages to cut this square, but Mohammed's sharp at point. A diving stop from the captain
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, comes down the wicket and drives to long on for a walking single
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: full outside leg, Sarfraz misses the sweep. But so does the keeper. No bat, no gloves, nothing, and the ball dribbles down fine to the boundary. Free runs
Commentary_short: Badree to Sarfraz Ahmed, 5 wides

Commentary: full on middle stump, turned off his toes to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Badree to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: beautiful delivery! Full on off, and it's the wrong'un. Goes away from Talat as he tries to defend. Well collected by the keeper
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, but stays low. Turned to the leg side with soft hands. Midwicket cleans up, but enough time to take the second run
Commentary_short: Badree to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: good length on off stump. Tapped towards midwicket off the back foot
Commentary_short: Paul to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full on off, and lifted over cover! Off the bat's toe end and intercepted by deep extra cover
Commentary_short: Paul to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: short on middle, forces the batsman to duck under this delivery. A well-directed bouncer
Commentary_short: Paul to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: full on leg, almost a yorker but Talat does well to get his feet out of the way. Squeezed to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Paul to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: low full toss just outside off. Mistimes his drive to Samuels at cover
Commentary_short: Paul to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, full just outside off. Caressed down the ground to long on
Commentary_short: Paul to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, and Sarfraz was waiting for that length. Takes his front foot out of the way, and swings over deep midwicket. Clean swing of the bat
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length just outside off. Powell takes the pace off again. Punched towards cover, but takes the inside edge instead. Goes to mid off
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle, and Talat smacks this with some power. Muscled to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Powell to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Mistimes his drive to mid on this time
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: slower-ball yorker on off stump. Dug away to point for a walking single
Commentary_short: Powell to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball outside off, but Sarfraz is know in the mood for the biggies. Carved over point
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: low full toss on off stump, bunted to deep midwicket. Tight from Emrit, not offering any width
Commentary_short: Emrit to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Tapped past Emrit's left to long off. Only a single
Commentary_short: Emrit to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: excellent! Yorker just outside off. Talat tried to ramp it fine, but can't connect
Commentary_short: Emrit to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: full on middle and off, tries to slog towards the leg side but not hit cleanly. Goes along the ground to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Emrit to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle, Sarfraz makes room but can only flat-bat it down the ground. Played to long on
Commentary_short: Emrit to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: another yorker on off. Bunted down the ground, but straight to Sarfraz. Hits the captain and ricochets to Emrit
Commentary_short: Emrit to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: slower ball full outside leg stump. Sarfraz makes extra room towards the legside but Powell followed him. Tapped to long on

Commentary: slower ball, and a low full toss on middle. Talat's through his shot too early. Miscued to long off
Commentary_short: Powell to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: clean as a whistle! Full on off, and Sarfraz gives that a big swing of the bat. Set himself up well by clearing his left leg, and then slogged it into the cow-corner boundary
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, SIX runs

Commentary: changes his length. Shorter just outside off. Sarfraz can't connect with the ball. Manages to flat-bat it to long on
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and leg, bunted to deep midwicket. Excellent from Rovman
Commentary_short: Powell to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: low full toss to end the over. The ball was dipping on the batsman this time, but manages to turn it behind square on the leg side
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, stands tall and drives this inside out past cover. Work for the man at long off, but he manages to cut it off
Commentary_short: Williams to Sarfraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: another mix up! And this time it's Talat. Some chatter between Kesrick and Sarfraz as Talat makes his way back. Full on off, and Sarfraz smacked this to deep midwicket. Talat turns back for the second, but Sarfraz doesn't think the run's there. Talat's in no position to get back at the striker's end. The chatter between bowler and Sarfraz was about a barge. They collided as Sarfraz turned for the second

Commentary: full on middle and leg, clipped off his boots to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Williams to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs

Commentary: full on middle stump, turned off his toes to square leg on the leg side
Commentary_short: Williams to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, driven past backward square
Commentary_short: Williams to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: another good-length ball outside off. This time he opens his bat's face and runs it down to third man
Commentary_short: Williams to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: low full toss on middle stump, checks his drive to long on
Commentary_short: Powell to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: paddled over short fine leg! Full on leg, and Sarfraz gets down on one knee and ramps it over the infield. Not easy to play that off the pacer
Commentary_short: Powell to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: holes out! Slower ball on off, and Sarfraz can't hold back anymore. Tries to slog it towards the leg side, but doesn't have the distance. Fletcher manning the boundary at long on

Commentary: slower ball, yorker on middle stump. Flicked off his toes to deep midwicket and straight to Kesrick Williams. But, oh dear! The ball slips through his fingers! Powell won't be pleased one bit
Commentary_short: Powell to Shoaib Malik, FOUR runs

Commentary: cutter on middle stump, takes the pace off once again. Tapped to long on for a walking single
Commentary_short: Powell to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: welcomed to international cricket with a yorker. On off stump, and dug back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Powell to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: played on! Good length, but wide outside off. Asif tries to drive this away from his body, but inside-edged onto his stumps. They're checking for the no ball, but the bowler's fine
Commentary_short: Paul to Asif Ali, OUT

Commentary: full and straight to Faheem. Defended back to Paul. Two dots to start the 18th
Commentary_short: Paul to Faheem Ashraf, no run

Commentary: dropped? Well, it'll go down as a missed chance. Low full toss on off, and Faheem muscles this back. Comes off the bat's top half, and Keemo goes diving forward to take a one-handed catch. Manages to only get his fingertips to it

Commentary: another caught-and-bowled chance dropped! Butterfingers this time. Full on off, and he's through his drive too early. Comes to Paul at a comfortable height, but he looked to clap at it while taking the catch. Not good technique, and drops this once again
Commentary_short: Paul to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: overpitched on middle, driven down the ground to long on
Commentary_short: Paul to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Slaps this past the infield on the off side to deep extra cover
Commentary_short: Paul to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle, and that's been smacked down the ground past Emrit. Terrific team-work between the two fielders in the deep, who combine to throw this back
Commentary_short: Emrit to Faheem Ashraf, 2 runs

Commentary: low full toss just on off stump, bunted down the ground past Emrit to long off. West Indies won't mind the singles
Commentary_short: Emrit to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off, and Malik creams this to the leg side. Pulled square, and Kesrick - at deep midwicket - misfields once again! The ball goes to the boundary and Kesrick looks hurt. Did he jam his fingers into the ground?
Commentary_short: Emrit to Shoaib Malik, FOUR runs

Commentary: classic Shoaib! Full on middle, and he manages to get under this ball. Uses his bottom hand to send this into the deep midwicket boundary
Commentary_short: Emrit to Shoaib Malik, SIX runs

Commentary: full outside off, and that's been slapped past cover! Man at deep extra cover races to his right but can't intercept. Big swing of the bat from Malik after opening his stance
Commentary_short: Emrit to Shoaib Malik, FOUR runs

Commentary: low full toss on leg stump, and this time Malik has sent this into the stands! Swivels and slogs this over deep midwicket. Excellent connection off the bat. Twenty-three runs off it!
Commentary_short: Emrit to Shoaib Malik, SIX runs

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Reaches at it, and manages to guide it past short third man. The fielder there gets his fingertips to it, but can't slow it off enough. Trickles down to the backward square boundary
Commentary_short: Williams to Faheem Ashraf, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on leg stump, and he tries to swing towards the leg side. Hits his front leg, but the ball goes past the keeper to the third-man boundary. Williams is appealing for the lbw, though, and takes the review. Did it pitch on the stumps? Nope, pitched way outside leg. West Indies lose the review, and that's four more to Pakistan's total
Commentary_short: Williams to Faheem Ashraf, 4 leg byes

Commentary: over long off! Fourteen off the first three balls. Low full toss on off stump and Faheem has no trouble to send this over the bowler's head. Rocked deep onto the back foot to make the full use the crease's depth
Commentary_short: Williams to Faheem Ashraf, SIX runs

Commentary: slower ball, full outside off. Mistimes his leg-side swipe to long on
Commentary_short: Williams to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: yorker on middle and leg, mistimes his clip-shot to deep midwicket. Played gently enough for them to take the second run
Commentary_short: Williams to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs

Commentary: good length on off stump, and that's been slogged to the leg side. Flat-batted, really, but manages to play it into the gap. Goes to the deep-midwicket boundary and Pakistan level their highest T20 score!
Commentary_short: Williams to Shoaib Malik, FOUR runs

Commentary: and that first ball disappears for six! It's not the greatest delivery, to be fair. A long-hop, angling into his body, and he simply opens up and pulls that away in front of square
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Walton, SIX runs

Commentary: shortish again, but quicker and flatter and not as short as the previous one. Hurries through and hits him on the body after sneaking under the attempted pull
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Walton, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, defended into the covers
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Walton, no run

Commentary: gone! Down the track now, sees a bit of flight, but he isn't quite to the pitch of the ball as he looks to hit this straight back over the bowler. Gets too much underneath the ball rather than behind it, and ends up skying it high and very straight. Long-off runs in a few yards, towards his right, and takes a fairly straightforward catch
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Walton, OUT
Dismissal_text: CAK Walton c Asif Ali b Mohammad Nawaz 6 (4b 0x4 1x6) SR: 150.00

Commentary: full on off, and defended back to the bowler. Walked down the wicket but tapped it back to Nawaz
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Fletcher, no run

Commentary: full on off stump. Prods forward, opens his bat's face, and glances it to point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Fletcher, no run

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Goes chasing at it, but misses the drive. Way too far for Samuels to make any contact
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, 1 wide

Commentary: good length on off, but jagging inwards after pitching. No footwork from Samuels, as he tries to punch down the ground. Hit to mid off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, no run

Commentary: good length on off, and the batsman slashes hard at it. Takes the thick edge, and flies over first slip. Well stopped by third man running to his left
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, 1 run

Commentary: soft! Straight to cover. Full on off, and he tries to drive away from his body. Looked like Fletcher checked his shot, and the ball goes to Talat at a comfortable height
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Fletcher, OUT
Dismissal_text: ADS Fletcher c Hussain Talat b Mohammad Amir 0 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: good length just outside off. Mistimes his cut with the ball going away from him. Only to point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Mohammed, no run

Commentary: full but just outside off, tries to drive over cover this time, but Mohammed doesn't have the elevation. Straight to Talat at cover once more! Windies in big trouble! The captain makes his way back. Almost a carbon-copy of the Fletcher wicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Mohammed, OUT
Dismissal_text: JN Mohammed c Hussain Talat b Mohammad Amir 0 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: good length on off, punched off the back foot to Talat at cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: full on off, and defended off the front foot. Comfortably played by Samuels
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Samuels, no run

Commentary: leading edge, but over point! Samuels would consider himself lucky there. Full on middle, and he tried to slog it towards cow corner. Through his shot too early, and the ball took the edge. But enough power behind his slog to take it over the infield
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Samuels, FOUR runs

Commentary: tossed up on off, and that's been smacked very hard down the ground. Nawaz manages to get his fingertips to it and reduce the pace of the ball. That must've stung!
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Samuels, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump. Ramdin takes a big stride forward and defends back to Nawaz
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Goes onto the back foot, and tapped to the bowler
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: full outside leg, and going down the leg side. Ramdin's happy to let it go
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Ramdin, 1 wide

Commentary: tossed up just outside off. Tentatively blocked off the front foot by Ramdin
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: slower ball, but full and wide outside off. Samuels looked to reach at the ball, but chose to let it go. A good choice from the batsman
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, 1 wide

Commentary: full on middle this time. Samuels slogs this towards the leg side, but straight to midwicket. The fielder takes a shy at the stumps (at the non-striker's), but can't get the direct-hit

Commentary: good length on middle and takes the extra bounce off the surface. Samuels tried to glance this fine but can't connect. Through to the keeper on the bounce
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, no run

Commentary: another well-disguised slower ball! Good length on middle, and goes across Samuels once again. Tried to play this fine, and takes a thin edge. But falls way short of Sarfraz
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump. Samuels tiptoes and defends towards cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump. Opens the bat's face and defends to point. No single on offer
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Samuels tries to run this fine past backward point, but stopped by Shadab!
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Samuels, no run

Commentary: wicket first ball! Taken at midwicket. Third duck of the innings. Full on middle, and he tried to clip it off his pads. Managed to get a good piece of it, but didn't place it well. West Indies are in tatters

Commentary: good length just outside off, and Powell defends off the back foot. Offered the full face of the bat

Commentary: back of a length outside off. Angling into Powell, and defended off the back foot again

Commentary: shoulders his arms! How rare is that in T20 cricket. Good length outside off, and happy to let it go

Commentary: good length outside off, but tailing into Powell. Defended towards the non-striker and they want the run, but Hasan's prowling on his followthrough. They choose not to take the run

Commentary: wicket maiden! Good length outside off, and defended towards cover. Big gap between bat and pad, and the inside edge is almost chopped on

Commentary: good length on leg stump, Samuels goes to the leg side and pulls along the ground to deep midwicket

Commentary: good length just outside off, takes a step forward and defended off the back foot

Commentary: full just outside off. Defended with soft hands towards cover. Faheem races across to his left to try and stop the ball, and that distracts the batsmen from taking the single

Commentary: good length on off, tailing into his pads, and Powell flicks this off his pads past midwicket. Deep midwicket's chase in the deep is futile

Commentary: good length just outside off. Stands tall and cuts past cover to the man in the deep

Commentary: clueless! Full outside off, but turns inwards. Tries to drive but he's nowhere near the ball. The delivery sneaks through between bat and pad, and through to the keeper

Commentary: flat on middle stump, Samuels taps this off his pads to deep backward square with ease

Commentary: good length, just outside off. Defended off the back foot to the off side

Commentary: good length on off stump, Paul shuffles across to the off side and clips it to midwicket

Commentary: good length on off, and clipped to Babar at midwicket. Has a shy at the stumps, but misses. Overthrows too

Commentary: full just on off stump, and Samuels creams this square past midwicket. The fielder there's too straight, and West Indies earn four much-needed runs

Commentary: sliced, and taken at point! Tossed up on off, and Samuels tries to slog this over deep extra cover. The bat turned in his hand, and the shot comes off his toe end. Faheem composes himself before completing a not-so-easy catch with the ball swirling in the air

Commentary: full outside off again. Blocked back to the bowler off the front foot

Commentary: full on off stump. Tapped towards the non-striker off the front foot

Commentary: quicker ball! Full just outside off, and he's too slow to defend. Takes the inside edge and trickles away to short fine leg

Commentary: tossed up, full just outside off. Defended towards point with the bat's open face

Commentary: good length just outside off. Straightens after pitching and Emrit defends down the wrong line. Can't make contact, and he'll thank his stars that the ball didn't clip the outside of off stump

Mohammad Nawaz to Emrit, no run

Commentary: tossed up on off stump, big heave down the ground to long on

Commentary: full on middle stump. Big stride forward from Paul, and defended towards the leg side

Commentary: full just outside off. Takes his front leg towards the off side and taps towards midwicket

Commentary: extra bounce to end the over! Good length outside off, but straightening after pitching. The ball zips straight through and just past his outside edge. Sharply collected by Sarfraz

Commentary: good length just outside off. Defended back to the bowler

Commentary: good length, wider outside off. The ball takes the extra bounce and goes to the keeper. Emrit pulls out of the drive

Commentary: good length, but just outside off. The ball turns into him, and it's punched to deep extra cover. They want the second run, and eventually manage to scamper across

Commentary: short ball on off stump, and zipping through. Manages to defend it off the back foot

Commentary: full and wide outside off, gives it a big swing of the bat, and muscled down to wide long on

Commentary: full on off, heaved towards the leg side. Fielder at deep backward square gives it a chase to his left, and does well. His diving stop saves the boundary

Commentary: full just outside off. Defended with the spin to mid off
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Emrit, no run

Commentary: full just outside off, and Emrit gives it a big swing towards the leg side. It's hit well, but not well enough. Talat, inches inside the boundary, plucks the catch at deep midwicket. Talat's not sure if he's taken the catch cleanly. Did his back leg hit the fence? Replays suggest no and the umpire concurs.

Commentary: beats long on! Tossed up full on off, and muscled towards the leg side. Good connection off the bat as the ball soars beyond the boundary

Commentary: good length on off. Cramps him for space, and the attempted punch goes to the leg side

Commentary: good length just outside. Tries to defend but takes the outside edge. The ball goes down to third man

Commentary: short on off, tries to pull but off the bat's top half. Mistimed to cow corner
